# Documentation Standards

## Code Documentation
- Add comprehensive docstrings for all public functions and classes
- Use Google or NumPy docstring format consistently
- Include parameter types and return types in docstrings
- Provide usage examples in docstrings
- Document any complex algorithms or business logic
- Explain environmental data processing steps

## API Documentation
- Document all public API endpoints
- Include request/response examples
- Document error codes and messages
- Provide authentication requirements
- Include rate limiting information
- Document data formats and schemas

## Project Documentation
- Keep README.md updated with installation and usage
- Document CLI commands and options
- Include setup instructions for development
- Document environment configuration
- Provide troubleshooting guides
- Include contribution guidelines

## Scientific Documentation
- Document environmental data processing methods
- Explain data validation and quality checks
- Document measurement units and conversions
- Include data source information
- Document calibration procedures
- Explain statistical methods used

## User Documentation
- Provide clear installation instructions
- Include step-by-step usage guides
- Document common use cases
- Provide troubleshooting information
- Include examples with sample data
- Document configuration options

## Developer Documentation
- Document development setup process
- Include testing procedures and requirements
- Document deployment processes
- Provide code style guidelines
- Include architecture decisions
- Document API design decisions

## Environmental Data Documentation
- Document data collection methods
- Explain data quality standards
- Document data validation procedures
- Include regulatory compliance information
- Document data retention policies
- Explain data processing workflows

## Technical Documentation
- Document system architecture
- Include database schemas
- Document API specifications
- Provide configuration documentation
- Include performance considerations
- Document security measures

## Maintenance
- Keep documentation current with code changes
- Review documentation regularly
- Update examples when APIs change
- Remove outdated information
- Ensure documentation accuracy
- Test documentation examples

## Documentation Tools
- Use Sphinx for technical documentation
- Use Markdown for user documentation
- Include code examples in documentation
- Use diagrams and charts when helpful
- Include links to external resources
- Maintain consistent formatting

## Quality Standards
- Write clear, concise documentation
- Use consistent terminology
- Include appropriate examples
- Test documentation examples
- Review documentation for accuracy
- Keep documentation accessible
